		<hr size="1">It's like being married 50 times all at once.  Your spouses never tell you what's bothering them, they expect you to be telepathic.  You are expected to put your guild's interests before your own.  You have to keep a clear and objective perspective about everything, and you ABOVE ALL must listen to your own conscience.  Guildleaders must often make choices that are unpopular, because conscience dictates that it's the right thing to do.</P><P>Basically, the job is VERY hard.  So many people assume leadership of a guild and envision power and glory for themselves, and then find out later that it's not like that at all.  With power comes responsibility.  Remember that before you take on this role.<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
